a527 24
/**
 * distance_uncorrected
 *
 * compute and output uncorrected distance matrix.
 *
 * As it is now, each method is like an independent whole program in itself
 * making ulterior maintenance difficult.
 *
 * I do not want to divide the process in steps (like distmat) using
 * separate matrices: for a large number of sequences, the square
 * and linear matrices needed might add up to a huge amount of memory.
 *
 * But most this does is writing out the matrix. Distances are calculated
 * pairwise and *that* is/should be the only difference among each of these
 * subroutines. So we can refactor this by consolidating all distance
 * matrix logic in only one routine and separating method specific
 * code into pairwise distance computation routines that take two
 * sequences and return their distance.
 *
 * Not much info on the routines as you see for now. That is because my
 * next step will be the above refactoring.
 */
void distance_uncorrected(char *outfn, char **seqs, char **seqnames, 
    	    	    	  int nseqs, int seqlen, double gapwt)
d529 1
a529 2
    int i, j, k;
    int matches, gaps;
